n_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py`, `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py`, and `step2_build_possessions.py` call `load_game_dataframe()` directly, so request failures and `extract_team_context()` `ValueError`s escape as raw exceptions.","The seasonal scripts wrap the same fetch path with retries and then translate failures into status dictionaries or `failed_ids` lists instead of raising.","Because these are sibling data-processing scripts rather than clearly separate layers, a developer cannot predict whether the play-by-play boundary will raise, return `None`, or quietly classify the game as failed/missing."],"suggestion":"Define one shared script-level failure policy for play-by-play loads, such as a common wrapper returning a structured `LoadResult` with explicit categories, and use it across both one-off and seasonal scripts.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"mixed_failure_contracts"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The repository has no single shared contract for play-by-play load failures, so each script invented its own boundary behavior.","Retry classification is coupled to a broad shared exception tuple, which blurs transient transport failures and deterministic data/logic errors."],"likely_symptoms":["historical_season_missing_masks_transport_failures","retry_bucket_mixes_transient_and_data_errors","sibling_scripts_expose_different_failure_protocols"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}


