{"batch":"error_consistency","batch_index":12,"assessments":{"error_consistency":71.0},"dimension_notes":{"error_consistency":{"evidence":["`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` uses a string-status contract (`\"ok\"`, `\"missing\"`, `\"error\"`) for game processing, but `fetch_game_json_with_retry()` returns `\"missing\"` both for true 403/404 misses and for exhausted `RequestException` retries, so callers cannot tell absent data from transport failure.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` uses exception-based flow for the same play-by-play load path, but its retry tuple `RETRYABLE_PIPELINE_ERRORS` comes from `nba_pbp_utils.py` and includes `ValueError`, `TypeError`, and `KeyError`, so parse/schema failures are retried and then downgraded into `failed_ids` the same way as network outages.","The single-game scripts `build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py`, `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py`, and `step2_build_possessions.py` call `load_game_dataframe()` directly with no boundary handling, while the season scripts add retries and status remapping around the same function, so identical fetch/parse problems surface differently depending on which sibling script is run."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"issues":[{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"historical_season_missing_masks_transport_failures","summary":"Historical season pipeline reports transport failures as missing games and drops the cause.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["In `fetch_game_json_with_retry()` lines 88-103, repeated `RequestException` failures and non-200/non-retryable statuses both end by returning `(\"missing\", None)`.","`process_game()` lines 152-160 maps every non-`ok` result to `{\"status\": \"missing\"}`, so downstream totals cannot distinguish real absent games from download failures.","This loses the original exception/status context entirely, making seasonal error counts unreliable and harder to debug."],"suggestion":"Use a typed result or richer status object that separates `missing`, `retry_exhausted`, and `invalid_payload`, and carry the original HTTP status or exception message through to `process_game()` and the season summary.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"mixed_failure_contracts"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"retry_bucket_mixes_transient_and_data_errors","summary":"The 2024-25 pipeline retries and suppresses parse errors as if they were transient I/O failures.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","nba_pbp_utils.py"],"evidence":["`nba_pbp_utils.py` defines `RETRYABLE_PIPELINE_ERRORS` as `(requests.RequestException, ValueError, TypeError, KeyError)` at line 26.","`load_game_dataframe_with_retry()` in `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` catches that whole tuple on lines 33-41, so malformed payloads or missing fields are retried instead of failing fast with context.","`collect_parallel_tables()` and `retry_failed_tables()` then catch the same broad tuple on lines 109-116 and 131-138 and only append the game id to `failed_ids`, masking which failures were network problems versus code/data defects."],"suggestion":"Split transient fetch exceptions from deterministic parse/schema exceptions. Retry only request-layer failures, and surface parse errors with explicit context such as game id and failing field so callers can report them separately.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"mixed_failure_contracts"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"sibling_scripts_expose_different_failure_protocols","summary":"Sibling CLI scripts use different error protocols for the same play-by-play load boundary.","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","step2_build_possessions.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py`, `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py`, and `step2_build_possessions.py` call `load_game_dataframe()` directly, so request failures and `extract_team_context()` `ValueError`s escape as raw exceptions.","The seasonal scripts wrap the same fetch path with retries and then translate failures into status dictionaries or `failed_ids` lists instead of raising.","Because these are sibling data-processing scripts rather than clearly separate layers, a developer cannot predict whether the play-by-play boundary will raise, return `None`, or quietly classify the game as failed/missing."],"suggestion":"Define one shared script-level failure policy for play-by-play loads, such as a common wrapper returning a structured `LoadResult` with explicit categories, and use it across both one-off and seasonal scripts.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"mixed_failure_contracts"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The repository has no single shared contract for play-by-play load failures, so each script invented its own boundary behavior.","Retry classification is coupled to a broad shared exception tuple, which blurs transient transport failures and deterministic data/logic errors."],"likely_symptoms":["historical_season_missing_masks_transport_failures","retry_bucket_mixes_transient_and_data_errors","sibling_scripts_expose_different_failure_protocols"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
